This paper proposes a technique for rebalancing link weights in decentralized credit networks, which involves designing efficient routing algorithms and ensuring network viability. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
